Neil Warnock has left Cardiff by mutual consent. The 70-year-old was appointed manager in October 2016 with the club second from bottom in the Championship and guided them to the Premier League in 2018. “Cardiff City can confirm that manager Neil Warnock has left his position by mutual agreement and with immediate effect,” read a statement on the club’s website. “Having joined the club in October 2016, Neil oversaw 144 matches and famously led us to promotion at the end of a fantastic 2017-18 season. The board will now begin the process of replacing Neil. An announcement to this effect will be made in due course.”